<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-5379] ProcessorContext.appConfigs() should return parsed/validated values</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5379</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5334&quot; title=&quot;rocksdb.config.setter must be a class instance, not a class name&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-5334&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-5334&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it was decided that the current behavior of &lt;tt&gt;ProcessorContext.appConfigs()&lt;/tt&gt; is sub-optimal in that it returns the original unparsed config values. Alternatively, the parsed values could be returned which would allow callers to know what they are getting as well avoid duplicating type conversions (e.g. className -&amp;gt; class).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13077248">KAFKA-5379</key>
            <summary>ProcessorContext.appConfigs() should return parsed/validated values</summary>
